Below is a worked‐through example of how to reproduce the pictured structure step by step.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) ANALYSIS OF THE TARGET IMAGE
• Block Count: There are 5 total blocks in the finished model.  
• Layers: The structure has 3 layers:  
  – Bottom Layer: Three blocks (blue on the left, red in the center, green on the right).  
  – Middle Layer: One long yellow rectangular block bridging across the top of the blue and green blocks.  
  – Top Layer: One orange “roof” piece centered on the yellow block.  

• Spatial Relationships:  
  – On the bottom layer, the tall blue block (left) and the green block (right) sit at the same height, with a red arch‐shaped block in between.  
  – The long yellow block rests across the tops of the blue and green blocks (and above the red one).  
  – An orange triangular wedge is placed on top of the yellow block to form the “roof.”  

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2) SELECTING THE REQUIRED BLOCKS (NO ROTATION ALLOWED)

Based on color, shape, and orientation, the correct dictionary blocks are:

• Blue Block (bottom left) → Block #6 (blue cube)  
• Red Block (bottom center, arch visible from the front) → Block #1 (red arch oriented with the arch underside facing forward)  
• Green Block (bottom right) → Block #7 (green cube)  
• Yellow Block (spanning the top) → Block #11 (yellow rectangular prism in horizontal orientation)  
• Orange Roof Wedge → Block #16 (orange triangular wedge oriented “upright” as in the dictionary)  

Hence, the indices used are: 1, 6, 7, 11, and 16.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3) STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER

{
  Step1: Move block with index 6   // place the blue cube on the left  
  Step2: Move block with index 1   // place the red arch block in the center  
  Step3: Move block with index 7   // place the green cube on the right  
  Step4: Move block with index 11  // lay the yellow rectangular block on top of the blue & green  
  Step5: Move block with index 16  // finish by placing the orange wedge (roof)  
}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Following this plan (using exactly the listed blocks in the given orientations) will replicate the target structure exactly.
